Ad Text:
3 + 3 month contract - March start
Obtain your Baseline Security Clearance
Levies Administration & Compliance business area

Our client, a large Federal Government Department, who enhance agriculture industries, forestry, trade and biosecurity require the services of a Senior Business Analyst for a short 3 + 3 month contract.

Duties of the Senior Business Analyst

Identify, investigate, & analyse business processes, procedures & work practices relating to the collection, administration & disbursement of primary industries levies & charges. This may include but is not limited to cloud-based software options, contemporary system architecture, & user functionality;
Identify & evaluate inefficiencies & recommend optional business practices & system functionality & behaviour, including to the external levies system interface;
Use project management methodologies, principles, & techniques to develop project plans & to cost, resources & manage the delivery of the system & software provider requirements;
Take responsibility for deploying functional solutions, for example creating, adopting & implementing system test plans to ensure acceptable quality & integrity of the systems & to identify gaps in user & training documentation;
Develop functional specifications for use by system developers;
Use data & process modelling techniques to create clear system specifications for the design & development of system software.

Skills and Experience Required

Proven experience using analytical techniques & tools to analyse & categorise data, ideally in the business service mapping domain;
Demonstrated ability to communicate complex problems & evidence-based analysis to stakeholders in verbal & written format describing current & future state environments;
Familiarity with cloud-based data solutions & platforms (desired);
Experience in technical writing & delivering clear, detailed documentation for consumption by a broad stakeholder audience (desired).

